So using the equation here.

I = mass * (trackwidth / 2) * (ka_ang / ka_lin)

to estimate the moment of inertia of a robot.

I have a swerve drive whose width is longer than the length. Should we average the 2 for the trackwidth or use the longest/shortest?

Max Motor Torque and Max Motor Velocity require some manual tuning unfortunately, due to compromises in the robot’s physics model, which assumes the robot can be simultaneously applying the max torque to accelerate while at its max velocity. This means Max Torque needs to be lower than ktcurrent limit. I run 0.63 Nm as a good starting point for drive motors.
